    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#boardman-hayes1966"/>, p. 169, n. <citedRange>1338</citedRange> (ph., dr.)</bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#cdl1970"/>, pp. 246-247, n. <citedRange>13</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>002100</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Θεοκ_"><seg part="I">Θεοκ</seg></name><gap reason="lost" quantity="10" unit="character" precision="low"/></persName> <unclear>τᾶι</unclear> <w lemma="θεά">θεο͂ι</w>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p><app loc="1"><rdg resp="#boardman-hayes1966"><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-60766"><name>Θεοκ<supplied reason="lost">λε͂ς</supplied></name></persName><supplied reason="lost"> μ᾿ἀνέθηκ</supplied><unclear>ε</unclear> 
                    <unclear>τᾶι</unclear> θεο͂ι <note>Boardman</note></rdg></app></p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p> Theok<gap reason="lost" quantity="10" unit="character" precision="low"/> à la déesse.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p> Theok<gap reason="lost" quantity="10" unit="character" precision="low"/> to the goddess.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p> Theok<gap reason="lost" quantity="10" unit="character" precision="low"/> alla dea.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Undoubtedly a dedication. But the lacuna might have included another name, such as <foreign xml:lang="grc">Θεοκράτης</foreign>. Moreover 
                    this name might be either the individual name or perhaps, although not so frequent, the father's name. On the other hand the verb of dedication was possible but not necessary.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
